{"session_id":"svc-1778079118250101373","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-06T14:52:02.33110557Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","resolved_harness":"codex","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"gpt-5.4-mini","work_dir":"/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-5ca2b0af-20260506T145155-81a3996a","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260506T145155-81a3996a/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260506T145155-81a3996a/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If you write `.ddx/executions/20260506T145155-81a3996a/no_changes_rationale.txt`, it MUST carry one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;one-line shell command\u0026gt;` — the loop runs it (cwd = project root, 60s); exit 0 closes the bead, non-zero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: needs_investigation` + `reason: \u0026lt;why\u0026gt;` — bead stays open for triage.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Bare rationales (\u0026#34;nothing to do\u0026#34;) are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260506T145155-81a3996a/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260506T145155-81a3996a/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Bead overrides project defaults\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead description and AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and conservative project defaults (YAGNI, DOWITYTD, no-docs-unless-asked) in this worktree — write whatever the bead asks for.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-5ca2b0af\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003ebeads: sort ready queues by queue-rank within priority\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;FEAT-004 and SD-004 now require `queue-rank` to order ready beads within a priority bucket, but the store still ignores queue-rank. Operators currently have to change `priority` to force a bead to the top, which changes urgency semantics and can reorder unrelated work.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\u0026#xA;- docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-004-beads.md:104-119 defines canonical ready-queue ordering as priority, queue-rank, created_at, id, and says queue-rank must not cross priority or bypass execution filters.\u0026#xA;- docs/helix/02-design/solution-designs/SD-004-beads-tracker.md:196-209 defines the same deterministic queue derivation and numeric compatibility rules.\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/bead/store.go:1346-1355 exposes Ready and ReadyExecution, but both delegate to readyFiltered without queue-rank-specific behavior.\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/bead/store.go:1702-1711 sorts only by Priority, CreatedAt, and ID.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;- Add a small queue-rank parser/helper in cli/internal/bead (acceptable names: QueueRank, queueRank, or parseQueueRank) that accepts integer values and numeric strings from Bead.Extra[\u0026#34;queue-rank\u0026#34;].\u0026#xA;- Update sortBeadsForQueue to sort by priority asc, explicit queue-rank asc with missing rank after explicit rank inside the same priority, created_at asc, then id asc.\u0026#xA;- Keep ReadyExecution filtering unchanged: blocked, cooldown, superseded, execution-eligible=false, and epic-only beads must be excluded before sorting.\u0026#xA;- Add focused store tests in cli/internal/bead/gaps_test.go or queue-specific test file.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Do not add queue-rank as a Bead struct field or known schema field.\u0026#xA;- Do not implement `ddx bead queue` CLI commands in this bead.\u0026#xA;- Do not change priority validation, dependency semantics, or claim semantics.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. TestReadySortsByQueueRankWithinPriority verifies an explicit lower `queue-rank` sorts before unranked and higher-ranked beads of the same priority.\u0026#xA;2. TestReadyExecutionSortsByQueueRankWithinPriority verifies ReadyExecution uses the same queue-rank order after execution-ready filtering.\u0026#xA;3. TestQueueRankDoesNotCrossPriorityBoundary verifies a ranked P1 bead never sorts before an unranked P0 bead.\u0026#xA;4. TestQueueRankMissingSortsAfterExplicitRankWithinPriority verifies missing queue-rank sorts after explicit ranks in the same priority bucket.\u0026#xA;5. TestQueueRankNumericStringCompatibility verifies numeric-string queue-rank values are read compatibly.\u0026#xA;6. WIRED-IN: sortBeadsForQueue, used by Ready and ReadyExecution, calls the queue-rank helper before created_at/id tie-breakers.\u0026#xA;7. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/bead/... -run \u0026#34;TestReady.*QueueRank|TestQueueRank\u0026#34; -count=1 passes.\u0026#xA;8. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/bead/... passes.\u0026#xA;9. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, area:beads, kind:feature, spec:FEAT-004, triage:no-changes-unverified\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-0a47840f\" spec-id=\"FEAT-004\" base-rev=\"b22685e0eca8d7bbb84656d03c3ee5d32ae28451\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260506T145155-81a3996a\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"FEAT-004\" path=\"docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-004-beads.md\"\u003eFeature: Beads (Work Item Tracker)\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"attempt_id":"20260506T145155-81a3996a","base_rev":"b22685e0eca8d7bbb84656d03c3ee5d32ae28451","bead_id":"ddx-5ca2b0af","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260506T145155-81a3996a","correlation_id":"ddx-5ca2b0af:20260506T145155-81a3996a","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260506T145155-81a3996a/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"8e4f5f8827b94f2979cbd984ffc135653b95485b843364c89ecad7d63566f0ef","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-e4851f5b","worker_id":""}}}
